#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:1
msgid "Numark Mixtrack Pro II"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:4
msgid ""
"The Numark Mixtrack Pro II is the successor of {ref}`Numark Mixtrack Pro "
"<numark-mixtrack-pro>` and features the same hardware with some minor design"
" changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:8
msgid ""
"[Manufacturer’s product page](http://www.numark.com/product/mixtrack-pro-ii)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:10
msgid ""
"[Forum thread](https://mixxx.discourse.group/t/complete-mapping-for-"
"mixtrack-pro-ii-is-ready/14756)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:14
msgid "Mapping Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:17
msgid "1. Browser Knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:20
msgid ""
"Rotate the knob to cycle through folders and tracks.<br> **Press:** Same as "
"Back button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:23
msgid "2. Load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:26
msgid "Load the track selected in the library to the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:28
msgid "3. Back"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:31
msgid ""
"Cycles between the file structure and the music library in the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:33
msgid "4. Shift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:36
msgid ""
"Allows multiple control commands to be triggered when pressed and held first"
" along with other buttons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:39
msgid "5. Play/Pause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:42
msgid ""
"Starts and suspends playback.<br> **Shift + Play/Pause:** Activates *soft "
"start* effect if paused or   *brake* effect if playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:46
msgid "6. Headphone Cue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:49
msgid "Sends pre-fader audio to the Cue Channel for headphone monitoring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:51
msgid "7. Cue (Transport Control)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:54
msgid ""
"The behavior depends on the {ref}`cue mode <interface-cue-modes>` set in the"
" Mixxx preferences. **Shift + Cue:** return the play head to the start of "
"the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:57
msgid "8. Platter/Jog Wheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:60
msgid ""
"This capacitive, touch-sensitive jog wheel controls the audio when the wheel"
" is touched and moved. When the Scratch button is not active, use the wheel "
"to bend the pitch of the track. When the Scratch button is active, use the "
"wheel to grab and move the audio, “scratching” the track as you would with a"
" vinyl record. You can also grab the non-touch-sensitive outer wheel to bend"
" the pitch of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:67
msgid "9. Scratch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:70
msgid ""
"Controls the behavior of the platters. When not active, the platter will "
"function as Pitch Bend. When active, the platter will have the ability to "
"scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:74
msgid "10. Pitch Fader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:77
msgid "Controls the tempo (speed) of the individual decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:79
msgid "11. Pitch Bend -"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:82
msgid ""
"Press and hold to momentarily reduce the speed of the track.<br> **Shift + "
"Pitch Bend -:** Toggles keylock on/off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:85
msgid "12. Pitch Bend +"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:88
msgid ""
"Press and hold to momentarily increase the speed of the track.<br> **Shift +"
" Pitch Bend +:** Changes pitch fader range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:91
msgid "13. Sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:94
msgid "Enables BPM syncing between decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:96
msgid "14. Effect Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:99
msgid ""
"Adjusts effect metaknobs.<br> **Shift + Effect Control:** Selects effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:102
msgid "15. Beats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:105
msgid ""
"Adjusts the Dry/Wet mix of the EffectUnit.<br> **Shift + Beats:** Adjust the"
" deck’s QuickEffect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:108
msgid "16. Loop In"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:111
msgid ""
"Function of this button depends on the current Pad Mode.<br> **Shift + Loop "
"In:** Sets the current Pad Mode to “Loop Mode”.<br> **Loop Mode:** Press "
"this pad to set the beginning of a loop.<br> **Sample Mode:** Plays the "
"sample assigned to Sampler 1 (left deck) or   Sampler 5 (right deck).<br> "
"**Cue Mode:** If Hotcue 1 has not already been set for the loaded   track, "
"this control will set Hotcue 1 at current position in the   track. If Hotcue"
" 1 has already been set, this control will jump to   Hotcue 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:121
msgid "17. Loop Out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:124
msgid ""
"Function of this button depends on the current Pad Mode.<br> **Shift + Loop "
"Out:** Sets the current pad mode to “Sample Mode”.<br> **Loop Mode:** Set "
"the end of a loop.<br> **Sample Mode:** Plays the sample assigned to Sampler"
" 2 (left deck) or   Sampler 6 (right deck).<br> **Cue Mode:** If Hotcue 2 "
"has not already been set for the loaded   track, this control will set "
"Hotcue 2 at current position in the   track. If Hotcue 2 has already been "
"set, this control will jump to   Hotcue 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:134
msgid "18. Reloop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:137
msgid ""
"Function of this button depends on the current Pad Mode.<br> **Shift + "
"Reloop:** Sets the current pad mode to “Cue Mode”.<br> **Loop Mode:** "
"Deactivate an active loop. If no loop is active, this   will activate the "
"loop and start playback from its Loop In point.<br> **Sample Mode:** Plays "
"the sample assigned to Sampler 3 (left deck) or   Sampler 7 (right "
"deck).<br> **Cue Mode:** If Hotcue 3 has not already been set for the loaded"
"   track, this control will set Hotcue 3 at current position in the   track."
" If Hotcue 3 has already been set, this control will jump to   Hotcue 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:148
msgid "19. Loop x1/2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:151
msgid ""
"Function of this button depends on the current Pad Mode.<br> **Loop Mode:** "
"Half the loop size.<br> **Shift + Loop x1/2 when in Loop Mode:** Double the "
"loop size.<br> **Sample Mode:** Plays the sample assigned to Sampler 4 (left"
" deck) or   Sampler 8 (right deck).<br> **Cue Mode:** Toggles Hotcue Delete "
"Mode. Press this button, and then   press one of the other pads in the row "
"to delete that Hotcue.<br> **Note:** This button is lit when in Hotcue "
"Delete Mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:160
msgid "20. FX 1 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:163
msgid ""
"Toggle the 1st effect in the unit on/off.<br> **Shift + FX 1:** Sets and "
"starts playback of a 1-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:166
msgid "21. FX 2 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:168
msgid ""
"Toggle the 2nd effect in the unit on/off.<br> **Shift + FX 2:** Sets and "
"starts playback of a 2-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:171
msgid "22. FX 3 On/Off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:173
msgid ""
"Toggle the 3rd effect in the unit on/off.<br> **Shift + FX 3:** Sets and "
"starts playback of a 4-beat autoloop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:176
msgid "23. Tap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:178
msgid ""
"Allows manual entry of song’s BPM by repeated pressing along the beats   of "
"the track.<br> **Shift + Tap:** Sets and starts playback of a 16-beat "
"autoloop.<br> **Note:** This button will blink at each detected beat in the "
"track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:183
msgid "24. Channel Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:186
msgid "Adjusts the volume of the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:188
msgid "25. Master Gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:191
msgid ""
"Adjusts the volume of the main mix coming from the software.<br> **Note:** "
"This does not affect the microphone volume. Use the Mic Gain   knob to "
"control the microphone volume."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:195
msgid "26. Crossfader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:198
msgid "Controls the blend between the two decks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:200
msgid "27. High EQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:203
msgid "Controls the treble frequencies for the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:205
msgid "28. Mid EQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:208
msgid "Controls the mid range frequencies for the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:210
msgid "29. Low EQ"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:213
msgid "Controls the bass frequencies for the deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:215
msgid "30. Cue Gain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:218
msgid "Adjusts the volume for headphone cueing in the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:220
msgid "31. Cue Mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:223
msgid ""
"Adjusts the software’s audio output to the headphones, mixing between the "
"cue output and the main mix output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:226
msgid "32. Stutter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_pro_ii.md:229
msgid ""
"Press this button while the music is playing to jump back to the last set "
"cue point, creating a “stutter” effect."
msgstr ""
